description:
Overview

Why buy a 22-page book when you can get 104!? We’re coming at you with an all-new untold tale featuring Spidey and that magical master, Dr. Strange! The good Doc ain’t feeling so well, so here’s hoping ol’ Web Head can cure what ails him in time to fight off EVERY mystical demon in the universe! PLUS, a backup story featuring Man-Wolf, PLUS classic archive material, PLUS Spider-Man J! If we tried to cram any more story into this thing, we’d be arrested!
name: Big Game; The Goblin's Always Greener; The Spider and the Sorceror; Enter... Elektra!

description: Issue occurs between Supreme #30 - Supreme Apocalypse, Part 5 of 5 and Prophet #1 and concurrently with Youngblood #3 - Babewatch Part I

Lara Croft is about to meet her match, again. The ancient cities of Sodom and Gomorrah have been uncovered. Unfortunately Sodom lies on public property and Gomorrah lies on private lands; lands that will be sold to a condominium and casino developer unless Lara can find a way to stop that transaction from happening. Her options include an unlikely adventure and unusual allies.

Part 2 
Lara Croft is about to meet her match, again. The ancient cities of Sodom and Gomorrah have been uncovered. Unfortunately Sodom lies on public property and Gomorrah lies on private lands; lands that will be sold to a condominium and casino developer unless Lara can find a way to stop that transaction from happening. Her options include an unlikely adventure and unusual allies.

Artifact hunter extraordinaire Lara Croft is on the adventure of a lifetime, out to track down the Spanish Armada of 1550. Journeys is a twelve issue adventure spanning the seven seas, full of swashbuckling adventure like you've never seen!

This Issue: Washed ashore in a foreign land, Lara Croft finds new adventure and a subterranean city of gold. A land lost to the most ravenous explorers becomes Lara's unintended hot spot of adventure, as she takes on the concerns of a small village and follows a little boy into unknown territory. A territory known as "El Dorado".

Overview

From out of nowhere she comes: graceful, beautiful, ethereal. Is she real or is she a dream? Here's a hint: dreams don't pack semi-automatics!

Story

Ghost is looking for information on who killed her and she needs X's help to do it. The adventure leads her to the man who had her killed and his bodyguard. She also finds out her name and meets her parents and sister, Margo Cameron for the first time. Meeting them however doesn't trigger any memories.

For every answer Ghost finds she gets two more questions. Ghost leaves a path of carnage in her wake and does everything she can to save her forgotten family. She is going to need all her powers to make these monsters pay and to save the ones she once loved.
name: It's A Man's World

description: Modi Tyrson faces the one thing a big, strapping young Viking dreads: women problems! From the deadly dilemma posed by a gang of seductive Water Witches to a bone-crushing confrontation with a single, renegade Valkyrie, Modi is challenged by one angry female after another. What is a Viking to do? And if that's not enough trouble, Loki, the God of Lies, in on hand to dole out advice and guidance to the young hero. This is bound to be educational! Witches, gods, giants, Valkyries, and armies of berserker warriors are all on hand to turn Modi away from his ultimate goal: entrance to Asgard and a chance to go mano-a- mano with Thorr himself! This issue displays a striking cover by Adam Hughes with what might just be the bloodiest comic book cover image of all time!
name: Falling for Gods

description: Reprints X-Men #15
name: Prisoners of the Mysterious Master Mold

description: Reprints X-Men #12
name: The Origin of Professor X

description:
The Inhumans are celebrating their centennial Water Festival, a sacred tradition "that celebrates life". They have invited other heroes (and villains) to the Blue Area of the Moon to celebrate with them. The Watcher observes and serves as the narrator.

Note: In the page depicting Banshee and Siryn as a singing duo, the woman by their side, holding her ears and clearly suffering is Moira MacTaggert.
name: Come to the Moon and View Heavenly Bodies

deck: "Join New York's prettiest detective, Jennifer Mays, and true crime writer Gabriel Webb, in a fair-play whodunit that challenges you to solve the mystery as it unfolds!"
description: When international art thief The Rogue decides to come out of retirement for one last heist, the gallery calls on Jennifer Mays, an ex-CIA operative turned New York City private detective, to stop him. Things get really weird when The Rogue steals the frames but leaves the paintings. Together with her new love interest, crime novelist Gabriel Webb, Jennifer falls into a web of intrigue.
name: The Adventure of the Rogue's Gallery

description:
Young Captain Adventure (Episode 2: X-Cessive Proposal)
 
The sex continues between Hericane and Young Captain Adventure and they take it to the skies where the vigorous love-making takes place in mid-flight (much to the dismay of a miserable New Yorker complaining about the downpour of sticky stuff) and as the two naked superheroes relax on a cloud, Darkblood fires a blast into the cloud from his office building, making sure that it was legal due to their indecent behavior in his airspace, and Young Captain Adventure plummets to the Earth. Hericane also falls, and manages to land naked in an alleyway where a man's lover has just broken up with him. However, just when he thinks it's his lucky day she flies off to the Team Supreme headquarters where she asks her team to help her rescue the kidnapped Captain Adventure. The team is too concerned about their income and refuse to help Hericane so she takes matters into her own hands and bursts into Darkblood's office where he promises to return Joey to her if she agrees to spend one night with him. She agrees and their lawyers negotiate the profits and the whole thing gets set up on Pay-Per-View for $69.95. Unfortunately for Darkblood, only moments into their passionate on-screen sex, Hericane takes things to the next level and it's a little rougher then he could handle. So, to save his own penis from certain destruction he gives in to her demand about the whereabouts of Joey, and it turns out Darkblood never captured him in the first place and someone else had gotten to him first. The story ends with Joey captured by a villainess who goes by the name, Bad Girl!

Doctor Dare and the Spear of Destiny (Episode I: Elenore & Franklin)
 
It's 1939, and in the basement of the White House, FDR watches as Joanna Dare demonstrates her newfound abilities on a group of soldiers. He finally calls it off at the bidding of his wife and he asks Dr. Dare to come with him to the Oval Office where they can discuss things in private. She goes over the origins of her abilities, seen last issue, and offers her services to America in this War. But the President refuses, in part due to her being a woman, and because America is still neutral in this war. He then has her proposal filed away with a numerous amount of files that would intrigue any conspiracy theorist. Back in Germany, Agent D dominates another woman and after receiving her sexual satisfaction, kills her, all before her Fuhrer. She then asks Hitler what will be done of Joanna Dare but he is more intent on the Spear of Destiny and commands her to go to Africa and fetch it for him. Back in the White House, a dinner party is being thrown in the anniversary of Teddy Roosevelt's death and in attendance is Pat Pike (Captain Adventure). He exits the party early to have sexual intercourse with Joanna Dare, initiating her change into her super-powered form. Then, in walks Eleanor Roosevelt. She waits for them to dress themselves then informs them of their mission to go to Central Africa and rescue American spy, Amelia Earhart. Pat is at first wary of partnering with Joanna but after she demonstrates her powers, he seems complacent. While flying over Africa the next day, however, Agent D shoots their plane down and they are forced to parachute into African tribal territory, specifically a tribe who ties them to a stake and dances around them with torches...

Libby in the Lost World (Episode 2: Man of a Thousand Faces)
 
Libby has come to enjoy the sexual pleasures of her new husband, Ugah Boogah, but the city girl in her still dreams of returning to civilization one day and if that's to happen she's going to need to teach Ugah Boogah to shape up and fit in with some of the accepted norms in society, step number one, getting rid of his mask! He refuses and she decides it's war and goes through a series of scenarios in trying to unmask him, all of them failing miserably and during which she ends up coming across dinosaurs and other unpleasant environmental hazards until finally he begins to unmask when she becomes unsure if forcing him is a right decision. Suddenly a dinosaur foot slams down beside him and the unmasking is halted, her "sign from God".

Scion (Episode 2: The Chase)

Pets (Episode 1: There Was A Time...)

Click 3
name: Two

description: Boba Fett rockets onto the scene with blasters blazing in this stand-alone story featuring the galaxy’s greatest bounty hunter taking on a dangerous contract that proves deadly for all involved!  Summoned to settle the score between two warring factions, Fett quickly shows his employers the importance of always choosing the right tool for the job, and the folly of underestimating just how much damage and chaos a single Mandalorian can inflict. Once unleashed, Fett's drive to finish the job is unshakable, and both groups quickly realize they’re dealing with a bigger and much deadlier mutual problem—one that must be stopped before it obliterates everything!  Don’t miss this essential piece of the Boba Fett mythos written by Thomas Andrews (Star Wars: Empire) and illustrated with the eye-popping art of Francisco Ruiz Velasco (Lone Wolf 2100).
name: Overkill

description: The biggest and baddest is back and ready to go ballistic. Greg Capullo, Spawn artist supreme returns to his original creator-owned project with a vengeance and to the man-monster that has wowed fans for years!
name: Out For Blood

description: Nyx has started to rebuild the world in her image. Vampirella, Passion and Squash attack Nyx’s followers to send her a message. Hunter is killed by Nyx and Hemorrhage. Vampirella seeks alliance with demon named Oliver, who has joined Nyx already. Nyx kills Cain who carries Hellworm. Hemorrhage leads attack to Danse base.
name: The Nature of the Beast

description:
Overview

Three of the most talked-about writers in comics team up with the talented artists of Gaijin Studios to bring you this star-studded Special. The Authority leader Jack Hawksmoor is spotlighted in a tale by Warren Ellis, Cully Hamner and Karl Story. Another Authority member, the Engineer, gets the focus in a tale by Paul Jenkins, Georges Jeanty & Story. Finally, the Wildcats' sword-wielding Zealot is featured in a story by Brian Azzarello, Brian Stelfreeze and Story. Plus, pin-ups by Jason Pearson, Joe Philips, Jason Martin, Chris Sprouse, Tony Harris and more.

Ares, the god of war has a whacked out follower, who is turning Gotham into Aresopolis. Can the Batman Family and The Wonder Family team up to stop him and Eris and Phobos and Demios from taking over the whole of Gotham?
name: Gods of Gotham

description:
Collecting the first seven issues of Phil Jimenez's critically-acclaimed run and the "Who is Troia?" story from. This trade paperback features the 4-part "Gods of Gotham" storyline guest-starring Batman, Nightwing, Robin, Huntress, and others. Plus, an Amazon civil war nearly destroys Paradise Island, and Lois Lane gets the scoop on during a "day in the life" of Wonder Woman.

This is a collection of Wonder Woman (1987) #164-#170 & Wonder Woman Secret Files and Origins (1998) #2
name: Paradise Lost

description:
Wonder Woman's world is falling to pieces. Her home of Paradise Island has faced a devastating civil war, and her mother, Queen Hippolyta, has abolished the monarchy, ending Diana's status as a princess. But the Amazing Amazon must contend with far worse in the adventures that confront her. Acclaimed writer/artist Phil Jimenez (New X-Men) is joined by inker Andy Lanning and cover artist Adam Hughes for one of the most difficult chapters of Diana's life. With additional art by Travis Moore, Brandon Badeaux and others, this story reveals a dear friend of Diana's transformed into a deadly enemy; a new, more menacing Cheetah; an intergalactic war - with terrible consequences for our heroine; and the return of an arch-nemesis that may spell doom for the male super-heroes of the world. The relentless onslaught is almost too much for Wonder Woman to bear! Arguing with her mother becomes the least of Diana's concerns as she joins countless heroes in the battle against Imperiex. And when Circe initiates her revenge against the Amazon, the world's super-heroines join Diana in a fight against the evil witch and several other female super-villains. With battle after battle facing Wonder Woman, is there any hope that Diana can find paradise?

This is a collection of Wonder Woman (1987) #171-#177 & Wonder Woman Secret Files and Origins (1998) #3
name: Paradise Found

description:
The road to the World Warrior Tournament begins here! Catch up on the first titanic Street Fighter series in this special recap issue. As Ryu arrives in India to find the legendary Dhalsim, he reflects on the challenges he has faced so far, and readies himself for all that is to come!

With only himself to rely on, Ryu continues to travel the world searching for answers. His journey brings him to India where he reflects back on his younger training days with Master Gouken and Ken, as well as his last encounter with Akuma.

The Human Torch is chasing a Pterodactyl around the Chrysler Building. A Brontosaurus is dragging The Thing down 5th Avenue. The Invisible Girl is trying to make a Tyrannosaurus stop chewing on her husband. Dinosaurs have come to New York, and they're not planning on going extinct this time!
name: Shortcut

description:
THE SIEGE OF WUNDAGORE PART 5. In their climactic battle against the High Evolutionary and his hordes of half-beasts, the Heroes for Hire and the Knights of Wundagore face their greatest challenge yet! Will the heroes be able to destroy Isotope E, the strange substance responsible for their transformations? Plus, Bova proves she can hold her own in battle!

Continued from Quicksilver #12
name: The Siege of Wundagore, Part 5: Final Conflict

description: Underground action rules the day when the Fantastic Four go head-to-head with the Mole Man! Strange tentacles and other weird stuff has been popping out of the New York City streets. The FF want to get to the bottom of it—literally! But when they tunnel to the Mole Man’s subterranean territory, even more fantastic surprises are in store...
name: The Things Below; Franklin Richards, Son of a Genius: Weather or Not

description: The Fantastic Four have encountered big menaces, but the ego of the Submariner may be their hugest foe yet! The monarch of the seas seeks a bride, and has set his sights on the world's most Fantastic girl!
name: Women are from Venus, Men are from Atlantis

description:
"Lost Souls"

Superman and Lord Satanus have a showdown over the soul of Metropolis ; Lucy Lane has a baby, it's a boy!

"2001 7"--Superman "S" in upper left hand corner.
name: Metropolis: Hell of a Town

description: "Cult of Persuasion" Part 2 of 2. Fight, fight, fight!!! The conclusion of Superman's battle with a man destined to make history begins with...the destruction of the Planet!?!
name: Cult of Persuasion, Part 2 of 2  :  The Persuader's Punishment!

description:
This is the TPB collection of the 3-issue DC The Psycho.

In a world where the cold war developed as a contest between super-powered beings instead of nuclear weapons, Special Agent Jake Riely is tasked with keeping the super-powered "Psychos" under control. When Jake is betrayed, his only escape is to take the potentially deadly super-soldier formula and become a "Psycho" himself. Jake lives, changes, and gains new amazing powers -- and begins the hunt for the traitor.
name: The Psycho

description:
Lois vs. Superman? The worst thing that could ever happen to the couple has seemingly come to pass, and not all of the Man of Steel's powers can do anything to stop it! Plus, the threat of the Parasite lingers for one final bout!

Continues in: Adventures of Superman #579

"2000 22"--Superman "S" in upper left hand corner.
name: Superman's Enemy Lois Lane  : Superman Vs. Lois Lane!

description:
It's a "Super" Fantastic Voyage into Superman. Can a shrunken Team Superman and Atom save Superman?

Continues in: Adventures of Superman #580

This story arc is reprinted in Superman: Critical Condition (2003)

"2000 26"--Superman "S" in upper left hand corner.
name: Critical Condition, Part 1 of 4: Little Big Man

description: 1. The Super Stunt-Man (Superman vs Blackie Weever / written by Bill Finger) -- 2. Comedian's Holiday (Superman, Lois Lane / written by Don Cameron) -- 3. Private Pete (gag strip by Henry Boltinoff) -- 4. Superman's Master (Superman, Lois Lane / written by Jerry Siegel) -- 5. Laffs (gag strip by Henry Boltinoff) -- 6. The March (full text story) -- 7. Good Ol Judge Jalopy (gag strip by Jack Farr) -- 8. The Quicksilver Kid (Superman, Lois Lane, Mercury / written by Don Cameron)
name: Radio Berlin

description: Jake Riley hates superhumans. A lot... but he's got good reason. Because for the last several years, Riley has been an agent of SIN (the Super-Intelligence Network). He works hard, but it's a dead-end job and Riley knows it, because all the really good assignments go to the FCOs, the Freelance Costumed Operatives...a.k.a. the Psychos, for their wild, super-powered and unpredictable - albeit effective - methods. When Riley runs afoul of SIN, he's targeted by his own agency and, in order to survive, he's forced to become what he most hates...THE PSYCHO. Armed with specially designed body armor that gives him superhuman speed and reflexes, the hunter becomes the hunted...a one-man task force determined to eliminate SIN.
name: Chapter One

When Giants Meet (Superman meets Paul Bunyan, with Lois Lane : an imaginary tale / written by Don Cameron) -- 3. Clancy the Cop (gag strip by henry Boltinoff) -- 4. Superboy begins his search for the person who killed his friend. Can Deadman help the Kid solve the mystery of Guardian's murder?

Guardian is dead and Superboy is feeling bad about it. Not only that, he's seeing ghosts when he should keep his eyes on Shrapnel! Don't miss the ending of this issue!
name: Touched by a Guardian Angel

description:
1. The Oracle of Smallville! (Superboy vs Big Brain Bates) -- 2. Super Safety Boy! (Superboy) -- 3. Peg (gag strip b yHenry Boltinoff) -- 4. The Backwoods Boy (a story about Daniel Boone) -- 5. A Day in the Life of Dennis (full text article about Dennis Day) -- 6. Superboy Acrobat (Superboy's Workshop) -- 7. The Submarine Superboy! (Superboy) -- 8. Smokey the Fire-Preventing Bear Comes to the Rescue of Peter Porkchops (public service message starring Peter Porkchops and Smokey the Bear)

"Who will be the lucky boy and girl to spend a day with Superboy? See inside for the most sensational contest in the history of comics magazines!"

"Pulp Heroes" continues with this tribute to the romance magazines of the 1930s. In a story by Peyer, Castrillo and Ensign, Supergirl, stumped by inexplicable phenomena suddenly occurring all around Leesburg, turns to the Legion of Super-Heroes' Brainiac 5 for help. Unfortunately, Supergirl may be in greater danger when the young, super intelligent Legionnaire immediately falls head over heels for the Girl of Steel!

Includes "I Lied for Love" (By Tom Peyer, Anthony Castrillo and Jordi Ensign) and "Object of Desire" (by Chuck Dixon, Greg Land, and Prentis Rollins)
name: Pulp Heroes : Young Romance

description: When the U.S. Government arrives to tighten its reigns on Cadmus, Superboy is none too happy with the "changes" they're planning to implement. But he's just a cog in the machine, and this squeaky wheel ain't getting no grease. In fact, he's being shipped off to Compton, Los Angeles to deal with a threat so powerful that it has rival L.A. gangs flooding the streets...to play jacks? Surprises, Set-ups, and subplots abound as Superboy sets his sights on Scizmore.
name: Smells Like Rage

description:
“The Quest for Cosmic Boy,” part 5 of 5. The quest for Cosmic Boy concludes as Brainiac 5's secret is revealed! Plus, Lightning Lad's place in the Legion gets a shocking change, Supergirl spends her last day as a Legionnaire, and the trans-temporal menace of Evolvo-Lad intensifies!

This is the last issue of Supergirl and the Legion of Super-Heroes. This volume is continued in Legion of Super-Heroes # 37.
name: The Quest for Cosmic Boy: Epilogue

volume.name: Supergirl and the Legion of Super-Heroes

description: Catwoman says she isn't committing certain the burglaries that fit her style, in Gotham. Who`s copycatting her? Batman will have to help his female companion or feel the anger of the Cats!
name: Prowler : Catwoman on the Prowl!

description:
1. Superboy's Hall of Fame! (Superboy) -- 2. The Mysterious Plan (Captain Tootsie) -- 3. Weather Guide (Superboy's Workshop) -- 4. Superboy, Bodyguard! (Superboy) -- 5. Casey the Cop (gag strip by Henry Boltinoff) -- 6. Science Question Box (full text article) -- 7. Bebe (gag strip by Henry Boltinoff) -- 8. Superboy's Great Amateur Hour! (Superboy, Martha and Jonathan Kent)

Ma Kent: Trimming the hedges with his hand - that's our boy!

Pa Kent: No, ma. That's our Superboy!

It's been 50 issues and the Looney Tunes are as wacky as ever! 
 
In this jam-packed special issue, Daffy interrupts Elmer's hunting comic story in "Daffy's Shot at Stardom," Bugs flees from Taz at the fair in "State Hare," Porky Pig bulks up in "The Insult (That Made a Boar Out of Porky)," Tweety shows cat/bird relationships throughout history in "Tales of the Kitty," Foghorn Leghorn shows readers a day in his life in "King of the Roost," Bugs stops Marvin the Martian from taking down television in "Marvin Strikes Again," Sylvester bungles a trap meant for Speedy Gonzales in "Mystery Bait," Penelope the Cat flees to a tropical island when Pepe promises to see her at the Empire State Building in "An Air to Remember," and Wile E. Coyote gets a death ray in "Dated Reference."
name: Th-Th-The Gang's All Here, Folks!

description: In this issue, Dripalong Daffy and his comic relief sidekick Porky do battle with The Tazmanian Devil in "The Devilish Desperado"; Wile E. Coyote joins the Army in his latest quest to catch the Road Runner in "Coyote Commando"; and Daffy and Speedy race to keep their delivery jobs in "Speedtrap."
name: Got Duck?

description:
Collects Detective comics 27-50.

For over 50 years he has been apart of the American mythos. He was a sensation from the moment of his first appearance, and today he has archived an even more phenomenal level of popularity. In that uniquely American contribution to popular fiction, the comics book, only one other creation has rivaled the celebrity of Batman: that being the archetype of all comic book heroes, Superman. In fact, the heroes represent two sides of the same coin. Superman, a super-powered alien sent to earth to become our greatest champion. And Batman, whose brutal origin on the dark streets of Gotham City results in comics' most grim avengers. His earliest stories reveal Batman as he was initially conceived: a mysterious dark nemesis of crime, a non-nonsense vigilante driven by some inner demon to eliminate society's malefactors. Later, with the introduction of Robin, we are presented with the more human side of our protagonist. Not so fierce perhaps, but every bit as resolute. DC Comics is proud to present this definitive collection of Batman's earliest adventures. Assembled here are the first two years of his appearances in his first home. For fans both new and old of The Dark Knight (or of popular culture in general) THE BATMAN ARCHIVES will be an indispensable addition to their library. In this volume lie the seeds of a true American folk legend.
name: Volume 1

deck: "Join New York's prettiest detective, Jennifer Mays, and true crime writer Gabriel Webb, in another fair-play whodunit that challenges you to solve the mystery as it unfolds!"
description: Gabe Webb is so excited about the nine "lost episodes" of his favorite old TV sitcom that he doesn't care how they've resurfaced! Private detective Jennifer Mays begins her investigation when a crime is committed... and a corpse is the result!
name: Murder-The Lost Episodes

deck: "Join New York's prettiest detective, Jennifer Mays, and true crime writer Gabriel Webb, in another fair-play whodunit that challenges you to solve the mystery as it unfolds!"
description: Fasten your seat belts for this action-packed issue that puts our detective duo hot on the trail of a car thief! Not just any old car thief, mind you - this one has swiped a high-tech prototype that will have underworld kingpins reaching deep into their pockets to possess it!
name: The Case of the Vanishing Vehicle

deck: "Join New York's prettiest detective, Jennifer Mays, and true crime writer Gabriel Webb, in another fair-play whodunit that challenges you to solve the mystery as it unfolds!"
description: When members of the "Ripperologists," a private society of criminologists dedicated to the study of the most famous of slashers, start turning up murdered, could Jack be back, 100 years after his last killing, or is someone else responsible?
name: The Return of Jack the Ripper

description: After Order 66, few Jedi dare to venture outside the shadows—rumors of the dark and terrible Darth Vader haunting even their waking moments. Yet, some Jedi find this life of fear unbearable. Now, a small band of Jedi have agreed to meet and discuss what should be done to oppose the Empire and its Sith Lords. However, the Empire is always watching, and Vader himself is eager to confront any Jedi that might bring him closer to the whereabouts of his betrayer, Obi-Wan Kenobi. Prepare for Jedi versus Sith action unlike any seen since the Old Republic in this special one-shot follow-up to Revenge of the Sith!
name: Last Stand of the Jedi

deck: "Join New York's prettiest detective, Jennifer Mays, and true crime writer Gabriel Webb, in another fair-play whodunit that challenges you to solve the mystery as it unfolds!"
description: Cryogenics divides the family of a man whose attempted resurrection is tearing them apart! Is it an act of love, or inconceivable blasphemy?! Strong convictions lead to rather rash results and yet another murder case for the MAZE Agency. Meanwhile, Jennifer's personal life is no great shakes either - could Jen be seeing green where Gabe's concerned?
name: Death Warmed Over

deck: "Join New York's prettiest detective, Jennifer Mays, and true crime writer Gabriel Webb, in another fair-play whodunit that challenges you to solve the mystery as it unfolds!"
description: Jennifer plans the ultimate gift for Gabe as she stages a "locked room murder mystery" for him to solve at his surprise birthday party. She and all of her guests get more than they bargained for when a real murder actually takes place and Gabe gets to play, "pin the crime on the suspect"!
name: Double Edge

deck: "Join New York's prettiest detective, Jennifer Mays, and true crime writer Gabriel Webb, in another fair-play whodunit that challenges you to solve the mystery as it unfolds!"
description:
Now a certified "item," Jen and Gabe make a romantic retreat to Jen's beach-house on Long Island. An unexpected dinner date with an "old friend" who's in the process of writing a book exposes a past that Jen would much rather leave behind! Gabe is all ears, and so is a certain government intelligence group determined to stop the presses.

*This issue marks the last published by Comico. The next issue is published by Innovation continuing the same numbering sequence.
name: Hearts of Glass

deck: Join New York's prettiest detective Jennifer Mays and her boyfriend Gabriel Webb as they continue their Caliber Comics debut. The look of the series is updated for the new decade, but the mysteries are just as clever. It's a fair-play whodunit as told by series creator Mike W. Barr.
description: Forty years ago superstar glamour model Kendra Rhoades disappeared from the American media circus, giving up her life to live anonymously in Europe. When Nostalgia Magazine brokers a deal with her for her return, they hire Private Detective Jennifer Mays to retrieve her from the airport and confirm her identity. But when she arrives, three different women claim to be the former model. Things go from bad to worse when one of the Kendras retains Jen's old friend and rival private detective Devlin Brooks who ends up murdered. Now it's up to Jen and Gabe to solve the murder and the real identity of Kendra Rhodes before the murderer claims another victim.
name: The Two Wrong Rhoades

description: Jake Riley's already become the thing he hates the most...a Psycho! Now he's gone over to the other side to rescue Sonya...and destroy the organizations that ruined his life!
name: Chapter Two

description: Who is the cause of Jake Riley's troubles? The Psycho's found out and now he's going to make them pay!
name: Chapter Three

description: From the creator of GROUNDED comes a hero with a secret. The armored vigilante known as Fear needs an addictive anti-fear drug to battle his crippling anxiety disorder and fuel his war on crime. But a mysterious enemy knows his weakness. He's cut off Fear's drug supply, kidnapped his mentor and blackmailed him into backing off. Now it's up to Fear to battle withdrawal, rescue his friend and put an end to this before his dwindling dosage - and his courage - runs out.

Avengelyne returns with this new mini series featuring the stellar artwork of Rick Lyon! The Avenging Angel gets a taste of sword and sorcery when she is transported to a world filled with insidious evil and horrific creatures... a world known as the Dragon Realm! As Avengelyne is swept into this barbaric world she faces brutish warriors and powerful rulers. But those mortal foes are nothing compared to the vicious lizards that rule this land. Can she possibly fight off a huge fire-breathing dragon? If you have never tried out Avengelyne before, this series is a perfect place to jump in and see what fans are raving about!
Sequentially comes after issue #25

description:
Here we go ! The first real mission for the I.O.

The Deviants are sent to bring back some proofs about the sale of weapon on the black market by a terrorist. But during the fly, the plane explodes and all the members of the team are separated... Frostbite finds Sublime but she is hurted by one of their ennemy : Dirge !

description:
She's young, she's beautiful and she's the deadliest assassin alive. Her name is Onyx and she has been aimed like a gun at Avengelyne. But why would anyone want to have Avengelyne killed? This special prelude to #1 has all-new exclusive art featuring the first sword flashing encounter between the two warrior women. With stellar art by Rick Lyon and luscious colors by Nimbus, this is not a book you want to miss. Because when she takes aim, you can be sure Onyx won't.

After crashing, most of the team is rounded up by Dirge and put in custody. Tremayne is creating biological weapons for an unknown buyer. While he is dealing with the buyer, Sublime and some of the other members escape. It turns out that Deacon is going to force the team members to help him, even if it means shooting them. Finally, the weapons buyer is revealed to be Arthrax.

description:
Copycat escapes from her cell and works her way deeper into the I.O. facility rather than escaping. Sideways Bob is called in to help find her but he refuses. It is determined that Copycat wants to destroy the files on the DV8 members.

In this issue, all of Copycat's personalities are described as well.

description:
The Coven are back in their most action-packed epic yet! The lycanthropic Darkwolf has come seeking vengeance upon his sister Fantom, and Spellcaster is caught in the middle after she is bitten by Darkwolf and infected with his dreaded curse. In a desperate scramble against time, Spellcaster, Fantom and Scratch must fight tooth and nail against Darkwolf and his pack as they make their way across town to the one man who may be able to prevent Spellcaster from being doomed to life as a werewolf!

The spotlight falls on Threshold, the former team leader of the Deviants-humbled and wounded as he finds himself outcast amidst he ugliest corners of the greatest city in the world. Rescued by a homeless woman living under the worst of circumstances, Matthew Callahan slowly regains his strength and will to live, but also learns some harsh truths about his benefactor in the process... leading to an ending that's anything but happy.
name: Gone To Ground

description: It's a day off and a night out on the town for the Deviants, who pay a visit to a local club that caters exclusively to I.O. personnel... which means that even the most underage of them are entitled to admission. As usually happens with teenagers who can't hold their liquor, tempers flare, accidents happen and embarrassing moments abound. And then something VERY strange happens to Sublime... something so strange that it will come to affect even the members of GEN13.
name: Slipstream Prologue

description: SLIPSTREAM, the long-awaited crossover between the Gen-Active teams of DV8 and Gen13, begins here! The Deviants have a new team leader as Ivana sends them on a mission to retrieve an incredible power source -- but they're not the only ones after it! And unknown to all of them, they're already the victims of a catastrophic event which threatens to tear asunder the very fabric of reality! Follow the parallel events taking place in next month's Gen13 Annual.
name: Slipstream Part. 1

description: Gen13 artist Al Rio's most anticipated title ever has arrived! Exposure reveals the deadly hidden secrets around us, as two gorgeous females blow the lid off the truths we take for granted. With all the slam-bang, never-come-up-for-air action of a Hong Kong John Woo movie, Exposure begins with childhood friends Shawna and Lisa, long separated after a mother's suicide caused Lisa to experience "visions" of her spirit mom and develop sensitivity to incredible phenomena. One is now a uniformed cop who married and divorced a cop; the other, a doctor who delved into more metaphysical answers. In "Black Sabbath," the girls meet again when careers cross paths in San Diego. Abetted by smitten scientist Alan Wong and charismatic biker bud/computer whiz Graham Burroughs, the foursome leaps into an explosive, action-packed adventure against a swarm of age-old vampires and their 2000-year secret.

Gen13 artist Al Rio blazes into his second on-time/every-time issue! In "Mirrors to the Soul," those fabulous babes, researcher Lisa Shannon and cop Shawna Diaz, surrender their jobs to launch Para*Tech Research and uncover two maddening mysteries! One: A beautiful wife whose very soul is being ripped from her being, Two: Horrifying monsters who attack humans possessing a certain secret, and Lisa is their next target! BONUS: This issue reveals the lost story pages from the rare ashcan edition. This issue unveils part one of a multi-part adventure with perhaps the sexiest comics action babes of all-time!

Al Rio's smash-sensation series comes to Avatar in vivid full color! Hot off a stellar four issues with Image, this new series features Rio's beautiful women of mystery drawn more lusciously than ever. This special, 40-page, oversized first issue drops Lisa and Shawna in the middle of another paranormal mess as a billionaire is accused of impossibly horrific murders. This issue also features the women in a lingerie-clad photo session that are some of the hottest pages Al Rio has ever drawn! A perfect series for fans of Avengelyne, Danger Girl, and Gen13!

What if nursery rhymes and fables fell into the wrong hands? Would story-time ever be the same? The first ever GRIMM FAIRY TALES ANNUAL features six nursery rhymes and bedtime stories retold with the same terrifying twists that fans of the series absolutely crave! JACK AND JILL find that sometimes the term "undying love" should be taken literally. THE OLD WOMAN IN THE SHOE finds her years of dishing out torment might come back to bite her. PETER PUMPKIN EATER is just a simple man so in love with his wife he will do anything to keep her. LITTLE BOY BLUE realizes that betraying those near and dear can have dire consequences. In PINOCCHIO, we discover the true origin of the boy puppet and what troubles await his father. Enter a world where fairy tales and nursery rhymes will never be the same!

description: Taking a break from her magic lessons in far off lands, Giselle returns home to Nouveau City for a visit with her sister, Gen. Little does she know that her greatest admirer awaits her ? Domo, a masterless demon who's convinced that Giselle is the dark mistress he's waited all eternity for! You always hurt the one you love...and Domo's sure got a thing for Giselle!

Exploring the connection between sex and violence, the adaption of Little Red Riding hood confronts that line. The werewolf displays the lust and animal nature of sexuality while Red symbolises the innocence and purity of love. The hunter is the balance between them both, taking you back close to the original story of the brothers Grimm rather than the doused down version we know today, the true moral behind the story is displayed.

A young girl with doubts about losing her virginity to her pushy boyfriend reads a story about Little Red Riding Hood in a book she finds beside her bed. The story of the fairy tale character parallels her own, and the ending of the updated story teaches her a lesson, which feels all too real.
name: Red Riding Hood
